<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10216226>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Oxarthrius spiculatus sp. nov. (A-E. Male holotype - STP0599; F. Female paratype – STP0267) A. Habitus, ventral view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Habitus, lateral view. D. Antennae. E. Abdomen ventral view. F. Abdomen ventral view. Scale bars = 1 mm (A, C); 0.5 mm (B, E, F); 200 µm (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10216226/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10216228>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Oxarthrius spiculatus sp. nov., paratype male- STP0269. A. Head, dorsal view. B. Pronotum, dorsal view. C. Elytra, dorsal view. D. Abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bars = 100 μm (A, B, D); 200 μm (C). Abbreviations: vf, vertexal foveae; laf, lateral antebasal foveae; oblf, outer basolateral foveae; iblf, inner basolateral foveae; bef, basal elytral foveae; ss, sutural stria; mbf, mediobasal foveae; blf, basolateral foveae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10216228/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10216242>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Oxarthrius anthicoides (L.W.Schaufuss, 1887), Lectotype (MNHN, EC21543). A. habitus, dorsal view. B. habitus, ventral view. C. original labels. D. habitus, lateral view. Credits of the photographs: Christophe Rivier (Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Paris, France). Scale bars = 1 mm (A, B, D)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10216242/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

